tasks.description:
Gate scheduled-task FIRING on a real production environment, defaulting OFF for every non-production environment, while keeping task discovery/display working everywhere.

FILES:
- NEW: apps/server/src/services/tasks/resolve-firing.ts
- EDIT: apps/server/src/services/tasks/task-scheduler-service.ts (dispatch + SchedulerDeps/config)
- EDIT: apps/server/src/index.ts (compute mayFire; decouple subsystem gate from fire gate)

IMPLEMENTATION:
1. Add a pure function:
```ts
// resolve-firing.ts
export function resolveTasksFiring(input: {
  nodeEnv: 'development' | 'production' | 'test';
  explicitOverride: boolean | undefined; // DORKOS_TASKS_ENABLED if key present, else undefined
  schedulerEnabled: boolean;             // configManager scheduler.enabled (master switch)
  deployEnv?: string;                    // SEAM: future DORKOS_DEPLOY_ENV / platform var; undefined today
}): { mayFire: boolean; reason: string } {
  if (input.explicitOverride !== undefined) {
    return { mayFire: input.explicitOverride, reason: 'DORKOS_TASKS_ENABLED override' };
  }
  if (input.deployEnv && input.deployEnv !== 'production') {
    return { mayFire: false, reason: `non-production deployEnv "${input.deployEnv}"` };
  }
  const mayFire = input.nodeEnv === 'production' && input.schedulerEnabled;
  return { mayFire, reason: `nodeEnv=${input.nodeEnv} schedulerEnabled=${input.schedulerEnabled}` };
}
```
2. In index.ts: keep the EXISTING subsystem gate (whether to construct TaskStore + mount routes) so tasks still list/display. Separately compute `explicitOverride = 'DORKOS_TASKS_ENABLED' in process.env ? env.DORKOS_TASKS_ENABLED : undefined` (the presence check already exists at index.ts:251) and call resolveTasksFiring; pass the resulting `mayFire` into the scheduler.
3. In task-scheduler-service.ts: add `mayFire: boolean` to SchedulerDeps/config. `registerTask()` still registers crons (so getNextRun()/display work in dev). In `dispatch()`, early-return when `!mayFire` BEFORE creating a run. Log the `reason` once at start() (logger.info) stating whether firing is suppressed and why.

ACCEPTANCE / TESTS (apps/server/src/services/tasks/__tests__/resolve-firing.test.ts, table-driven, each case a named purpose):
- development + no override -> mayFire=false
- production + schedulerEnabled=true + no override -> mayFire=true
- production + schedulerEnabled=false -> mayFire=false
- development + explicitOverride=true -> mayFire=true
- production + explicitOverride=false -> mayFire=false
- deployEnv='preview' at nodeEnv=production, no override -> mayFire=false
- test env + no override -> mayFire=false
Scheduler integration: with mayFire=false a fired cron creates NO run, but getNextRun() is non-null (display intact).
Gate: pnpm typecheck && pnpm lint && pnpm vitest run apps/server/src/services/tasks. Ships the headline safety win independently.
